UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS SB 223/GA
1 AN ACT relating to the regulation of cannabis-infused beverages.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 SECTION 1. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 243 IS CREATED TO
4 READ AS FOLLOWS:
5 The holder of a cannabis-infused beverage distributor's license may, in wet territory:
6 (1) Sell and serve cannabis-infused beverages to consumers at bars, restaurants,
7 fairs, and festivals; and
8 (2) With a sampling license, serve complimentary samples of cannabis-infused
9 beverages to consumers on licensed premises and at bars, restaurants, fairs, and
10 festivals, not to exceed twelve (12) ounces per person, per day.
11 SECTION 2. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 243 IS CREATED TO
12 READ AS FOLLOWS:
13 (1) The department may issue a nonquota cannabis-infused beverage drink license
14 as a supplemental license as set forth in this section.
15 (2) (a) A nonquota cannabis-infused beverage drink license may be issued by the
16 department as a supplemental license for a retail drink licensee listed in
17 paragraph (b) of this subsection, if the licensed premises is located within:
18 1. A wet territory; or
19 2. Any precinct that has authorized the sale of alcoholic beverages under
20 KRS 242.1242.
21 (b) A nonquota cannabis-infused beverage drink license shall authorize the
22 licensee to sell cannabis-infused beverages by the drink and may be issued
23 as a supplemental license to a cannabis-infused beverage manufacturer
24 permitted by the Department for Public Health or the holder of a:
25 1. Quota retail drink license;
26 2. Nonquota type 1 retail drink license;
27 3. Nonquota type 2 retail drink license;
Page 1 of 24
SB022310.100 - 1523 - XXXX 3/20/2026 11:17 AM GA

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS SB 223/GA
1 4. Nonquota type 3 retail drink license;
2 5. Nonquota type 4 retail drink license;
3 6. Special temporary license;
4 7. Special Sunday retail drink license;
5 8. Caterer’s license;
6 9. Entertainment destination center license;
7 10. Limited restaurant license;
8 11. Limited golf course license; or
9 12. Qualified historic site license.
10 (c) Licensees identified in paragraph (b) of this subsection shall purchase
11 cannabis-infused beverages only from licensed cannabis-infused beverage
12 distributors or cannabis-infused beverage manufacturers authorized to self-
13 distribute.
14 (3) A nonquota retail cannabis-infused beverage package license may be issued by
15 the department as a supplemental license to a retailer that holds a permit to
16 operate a hemp retail establishment issued by the Cabinet for Health and Family
17 Services, provided the retailer derives at least seventy percent (70%) of its revenue
18 from hemp products and meets the criteria outlined in subsection (2)(a) of this
19 section.
20 Section 3. KRS 243.0307 is amended to read as follows:
21 (1) A sampling license may be issued to the holder of:
22 (a) A quota retail drink license;
23 (b) A quota retail package license;
24 (c) A nonquota retail malt beverage package license;
25 (d) An NQ1 license;
26 (e) An NQ2 license;
27 (f) An NQ4 retail malt beverage drink license;[ or]
Page 2 of 24
SB022310.100 - 1523 - XXXX 3/20/2026 11:17 AM GA

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS SB 223/GA
1 (g) A distiller's license;
2 (h) A cannabis-infused beverage retail package license; or
3 (i) A nonquota cannabis-infused beverage drink license.
4 (2) A sampling license shall authorize the licensee to allow customers to sample, free
5 of charge, distilled spirits, wine,[ and] malt beverages, and cannabis-infused
6 beverages under the following conditions:
7 (a) Except as provided in Sections 1 and 2 of this Act, sampling shall be
8 permitted only on licensed premises and by licensees holding a sampling
9 license, during regular business hours;
10 (b) A distillery shall provide samples as authorized by KRS 243.0305;
11 (c) All other licensees shall limit a customer to:
12 1. One (1) ounce of distilled spirits samples per day;
13 2. Six (6) ounces of wine samples per day;[ or]
14 3. Twelve (12) ounces of malt beverage samples per day; or
15 4. Twelve (12) ounces of cannabis-infused beverage samples per day;[
16 and]
17 (d) A brewer, microbrewery, or out-of-state malt beverage supplier may conduct
18 a sampling of malt beverages as permitted by this section at the licensed
19 premises of a retailer licensee holding a sampling license; and
20 (e) A cannabis-infused beverage manufacturer permitted by the Department for
21 Public Health or the holder of a cannabis-infused beverage distributor's
22 license may conduct a sampling of cannabis-infused beverages as permitted
23 by this section at the licensed premises of a retailer licensee holding a
24 cannabis-infused beverage retail package license or a nonquota cannabis-
25 infused beverage drink license.
26 (3) Retailers holding a sampling license shall:
27 (a) Notify the Department of Alcoholic Beverage Control at least seven (7) days
Page 3 of 24
SB022310.100 - 1523 - XXXX 3/20/2026 11:17 AM GA

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS SB 223/GA
1 in advance of conducting a free sampling event; and
2 (b) Limit a sampling event to a period not to exceed four (4) consecutive hours
3 between 12 noon and 8 p.m.
4 (4) In addition to free sampling, a quota retail package licensee holding a sampling
5 license may also sell sample distilled spirits and wine under the following
6 conditions:
7 (a) Paid samples may be sold only on licensed premises and by licensees holding
8 a sampling license, during regular business hours; and
9 (b) A licensee shall limit a customer to purchased samples totaling no more than:
10 1. Two (2) ounces of distilled spirits per day; and
11 2. Nine (9) ounces of wine per day.
12 (5) A quota retail package licensee holding both a sampling license and a nonquota
13 retail malt beverage package license may also sell samples of malt beverages under
14 the following conditions:
15 (a) Paid samples may be sold only on licensed premises and by licensees holding
16 a sampling license, during regular business hours;
17 (b) A licensee shall limit a customer to no more than sixteen (16) ounces of malt
18 beverages per day; and
19 (c) The retail price of a sample shall not be less than a licensee's purchase cost of
20 the sample.
21 (6) No customer shall be allowed to receive a combination of free and purchased
22 samples totaling more than:
23 (a) Two (2) ounces of distilled spirits per day; and
24 (b) Nine (9) ounces of wine per day.
25 (7) Free and paid samples provided under this section shall not constitute drink sales.
26 Section 4. KRS 243.401 is amended to read as follows:
27 (1) (a) The distribution and retail sale of cannabis-infused beverages shall be
Page 4 of 24
SB022310.100 - 1523 - XXXX 3/20/2026 11:17 AM GA

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS SB 223/GA
1 regulated solely by the Department of Alcoholic Beverage Control. The
2 department shall adopt and exclusively enforce the administrative regulations
3 of the Department for Public Health relating to the distribution and retail sale
4 of cannabis-infused beverages until such time as the Department of Alcoholic
5 Beverage Control promulgates its own administrative regulations on the
6 subject on or before July 1, 2026, including the establishment of fees to issue
7 a nonquota cannabis-infused beverage drink license.
8 (b) The distribution and retail sale of packaged cannabis-infused beverages shall
9 be regulated by the department. On or before July 1, 2026, the department
10 shall promulgate administrative regulations in accordance with KRS Chapter
11 13A to establish the rules and procedures for this distribution and retail sale.
12 (c) A local administrator shall only have authority over the distribution and retail
13 sale of cannabis-infused beverages in its territory to the extent expressly
14 authorized by KRS Chapters 241 to 244.
15 (2) Except as provided in Sections 1 and 2 of this Act, cannabis-infused beverages
16 shall only be available for retail sale:
17 (a) By the drink;
18 (b) By the package;
19 (c)[(b)] In wet territory; and
20 (d)[(c)] By the holder of[ both] a:
21 1. Quota retail package license;[ and ]
22 2. [A ]Cannabis-infused beverage retail package license; or
23 3. Nonquota cannabis-infused beverage drink license.
24 (3) A person under twenty-one (21) years of age shall not purchase or consume
25 cannabis-infused beverages. All restrictions and offenses related to minors and
26 alcoholic beverages in KRS Chapters 241 to 244 shall also apply in the same
27 manner to minors and cannabis-infused beverages.
