1 (4) If approved as a cannabis-infused beverage manufacturer by the Department for
2 Public Health, that manufacturer may:
3 (a) Self-distribute cannabis-infused beverages in the same manner as distilled
4 spirits; and
5 (b) Ship cannabis-infused beverages under a direct shipper license in the same
6 manner that a direct shipper license allows the shipment of alcoholic
7 beverages. A direct shipper licensee may sell or ship to a consumer all types
8 of alcoholic beverages and cannabis-infused beverages that the licensee is
9 authorized to sell.
10 (5) Cannabis-infused beverages may be shipped and delivered in the same manner as
11 alcoholic beverages.
12 Section 5. KRS 189.530 is amended to read as follows:
13 (1) No person shall provide a motor vehicle to another to operate upon a highway,
14 knowing that the other person is in an intoxicated condition, or under the influence
15 of any substance which may impair one's driving ability.
16 (2) A person is guilty of possession of an open alcoholic beverage container in a motor
17 vehicle, when he or she has in his or her possession an open alcoholic beverage
18 container in the passenger area of a motor vehicle located on a public highway or
19 on the right-of-way of a public highway. However, nothing in this section shall
20 prohibit the possession of an open alcoholic beverage container by an individual
21 who is strictly a passenger and not the driver, in the passenger area of a motor
22 vehicle maintained or used primarily for the transportation of persons for
23 compensation, such as buses, taxis, and limousines, or in a recreational vehicle,
24 motor home, or motor coach.
25 (3) A person is guilty of possession of an open cannabis-infused beverage container
26 in a motor vehicle, when he or she has in his or her possession an open cannabis-
27 infused beverage container in the passenger area of a motor vehicle located on a
Page 6 of 24
SB022310.100 - 1523 - XXXX 3/20/2026 11:17 AM GA

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS SB 223/GA
1 public highway or on the right-of-way of a public highway. However, nothing in
2 this section shall prohibit the possession of an open cannabis-infused beverage
3 container by an individual who is strictly a passenger and not the driver, in the
4 passenger area of a motor vehicle maintained or used primarily for the
5 transportation of persons for compensation, such as buses, taxis, and limousines,
6 or in a recreational vehicle, motor home, or motor coach.
7 (4) As used in[For purposes of] this section, "alcoholic beverage" means:
8 (a) Beer, ale, porter, stout, and other similar fermented beverages including sake
9 or similar products of any name or description containing one-half of one
10 percent (0.5%) or more of alcohol by volume, brewed or produced from malt,
11 wholly or in part, or from any substitute therefor;
12 (b) Wine of not less than one-half of one percent (0.5%) of alcohol by volume; or
13 (c) Distilled spirits which is that substance known as ethyl alcohol, ethanol, or
14 spirits of wine in any form including all dilutions and mixtures thereof from
15 whatever source or by whatever process produced.
16 (5)[(4)] As used in[For the purposes of] this section, "open alcoholic beverage
17 container" means any bottle, can, or other receptacle that contains any amount of
18 alcoholic beverage, and:
19 (a) Is open or has a broken seal; or
20 (b) The contents of which are partially removed.
21 (6)[(5)] As used in this section, "open cannabis-infused beverage container" means
22 any bottle, can, or other receptacle that contains any amount of cannabis-infused
23 beverage and:
24 (a) Is open or has a broken seal; or
25 (b) The contents of which are partially removed.
26 (7) As used in[For the purposes of] this section, "passenger area" means the area
27 designed to seat the driver and the passengers while the motor vehicle is in
Page 7 of 24
SB022310.100 - 1523 - XXXX 3/20/2026 11:17 AM GA

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS SB 223/GA
1 operation and any area that is readily accessible to the driver or a passenger while in
2 their seating positions, including the glove compartment. Passenger area does not
3 include possession of an open alcoholic beverage container or an open cannabis-
4 infused beverage container in a locked glove compartment, or behind the last
5 upright seat or in an area not normally occupied by the driver or a passenger in a
6 motor vehicle that is not equipped with a trunk.
7 (8)[(6)] As used in[For the purpose of] this section, "public highway" or "right-of-way
8 of a public highway" means the entire width between and immediately adjacent to
9 the boundary lines of every way publicly maintained when any part thereof is open
10 to the use of the public for purposes of vehicular travel.
11 (9)[(7)] No person shall, as a result of a single course of conduct, be tried for or
12 convicted of a violation of this section and a violation of KRS 222.202 or 525.100.
13 The attorney for the Commonwealth shall elect under which statute to proceed. A
14 conviction, decision not to prosecute, or dismissal of charges under any of these
15 statutes shall operate as a bar to prosecution under any other of these statutes for
16 offenses arising out of the same course of conduct.
