6 Section 8. KRS 243.033 is amended to read as follows:
7 (1) A caterer's license may be issued as a supplementary license to a caterer that holds a
8 quota retail package license, a quota retail drink license, an NQ1 license, an NQ2
9 license, or a limited restaurant license.
10 (2) The caterer's license may be issued as a primary license to a caterer in any wet
11 territory or in any moist territory under KRS 242.1244 for the premises that serves
12 as the caterer's commissary and designated banquet hall. No primary caterer's
13 license shall authorize alcoholic beverage sales at a premises that operates as a
14 restaurant. The alcoholic beverage stock of the caterer shall be kept under lock and
15 key at the licensed premises during the time that the alcoholic beverages are not
16 being used in conjunction with a catered function.
17 (3) The caterer's license shall authorize the caterer to:
18 (a) Purchase and store alcoholic beverages in the manner prescribed in KRS
19 243.088, 243.250, and 244.260;
20 (b) Transport, sell, serve, and deliver alcoholic beverages by the drink at locations
21 away from the licensed premises or at the caterer's designated banquet hall in
22 conjunction with the catering of food and alcoholic beverages for a customer
23 and the customer's guests, in:
24 1. Cities and counties established as moist territory under KRS 242.1244 if
25 the receipts from the catering of food at any catered event are at least
26 seventy percent (70%) of the gross receipts from the catering of both
27 food and alcoholic beverages;
