15 (f) A business located within, or adjacent to, an entertainment destination center
16 licensed premises.
17 (2) A holder of an NQ2 retail drink license may purchase, receive, possess, and sell
18 alcoholic beverages at retail by the drink for consumption on the licensed premises
19 or off-premises consumption pursuant to KRS 243.081. The licensee shall purchase
20 alcoholic beverages only from licensed wholesalers or distributors, except for
21 purchases made by restaurants pursuant to subsection (4) of this section. A distiller
22 may purchase its own products for retail drink sales under KRS 243.0305. The
23 holder of an NQ2 retail drink license shall store alcoholic beverages in the manner
24 prescribed in KRS 244.260.
25 (3) (a) To qualify for an NQ2 license, a riverboat shall have a regular or alternative
26 place of mooring in a wet county or city of this state.
27 (b) If a riverboat moors or makes landfall in a location other than its regular or
Page 17 of 24
SB022310.100 - 1523 - XXXX 3/20/2026 11:17 AM GA

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS SB 223/GA
1 alternate regular place of mooring, all alcoholic beverages shall be kept
2 locked.
3 (c) A riverboat licensed under this subsection shall not take on or discharge
4 passengers when mooring or making landfall in dry option territory.
5 (4) (a) A holder of an NQ2 retail drink license operating as a restaurant may
6 purchase alcoholic beverages by the package from licensees authorized to sell
7 distilled spirits, wine, and malt beverages at retail, but only if those alcoholic
8 beverages have first gone through the three (3) tier system.
9 (b) Any purchase made pursuant to this subsection shall:
10 1. Only be sold by the drink for consumption on the licensed premises or
11 off-premises consumption pursuant to KRS 243.081;
12 2. Be reported quarterly on a form prescribed by the department; and
13 3. Include a copy of each receipt of purchase.
14 (c) A holder of an NQ2 retail drink license shall not purchase at retail more than:
15 1. Nine (9) liters of distilled spirits per month;
16 2. Nine (9) liters of wine per month; and
17 3. Three (3) cases of malt beverages per month.
18 (5) A nonquota retail cannabis-infused beverage drink license may be issued by the
19 department as a supplemental license to an individual or entity that holds an NQ2
20 retail drink license in accordance with subsection (2) of Section 2 of this Act.
