12 Section 15. KRS 243.088 is amended to read as follows:
13 (1) A "Nonquota type 4" or "NQ4" retail malt beverage drink license may be issued to
14 the holder of a quota retail drink license, microbrewery license, small farm winery
15 license, or any other business wishing to sell malt beverages by the drink for
16 consumption on the premises only.
17 (2) An NQ4 retail malt beverage drink license shall authorize the licensee to:
18 (a) Sell malt beverages at retail by the drink from only the licensed premises for
19 consumption at the licensed premises only; and
20 (b) Purchase malt beverages only from a distributor, except for purchases made
21 pursuant to subsection (5) of this section.
22 (3) The holder of an NQ4 retail malt beverage drink license may also hold a nonquota
23 retail malt beverage package license.
24 (4) A nonquota retail malt beverage drink license shall not be issued to any premises
25 from which gasoline and lubricating oil are sold or from which the servicing and
26 repair of motor vehicles is conducted, unless there is maintained in inventory on the
27 premises for sale at retail not less than five thousand dollars ($5,000) of food,
